title: Thick Target Yields of 34M-Cl and 38-Cl Produced By Various Charged Particles On Prosphorus, Sulphur and Chlorine Targets.

x4freetext: THICK TARGET YIELDS OF 34M-CL AND 38-CL PRODUCED BY
VARIOUS CHARGED PARTICLES ON PROSPHORUS, SULPHUR AND
CHLORINE TARGETS.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.27, p.159 (1976)

x4codes.hlp: Fiziko-Energeticheskii Inst., Obninsk, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics
Fiziko-Energeticheskii Inst., Obninsk, Union of Soviet Socialist Republics

x4freetext: FOR THE DETERMINTION OF RELATIVE CURVE,THE
IRRADIATION WAS CARRIED OUT IN THE SPECIAL TARGET
DEVICE ROTATING 10 SAMPLES, AND BEFORE EACH OF THEM
THE MONITORING AND ABSORBING FOILS WERE PLACED.THE
ABSOLUTE VALUE OF THE THICK TARGET YIELD WAS
DETERMINED AT THE MAXIMUM ENERGY OF CHARGED PARTICLES,
THE IRRADIATION IN THIS CASE WAS CURRIED OUT IN A
TARGET DEVICE WITH FARADAY CUP. THE IRRADIATION TIME
WAS 15 MIN, THE BEAM INTENSITY 0.02 MUA.
. THIS IS THE UNCERTAINTY OF A DATA POINT
READER.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: . THE PERCENTAGE ERROR OF THE ABSOLUTE
VALUE OF THE THICK TARGET YIELD IS 15 PER CENT.
. BY CAYAD.
. BY B.V. ZATOLOKIN.
.B.V.ZATOLOKIN HAVE CORRECTED THE MISPRINTING.
